Dialogs.Dialog: I feel focused today. The difficult formulas easily come together.
Not good. The formulas and symbols make me drowsy...

I did very well with the experiment. I'm in perfect form！
I thought that the law of conservation of mass was always right. Guess I was wrong.
In the special theory of relativity, mass can be changed to energy and in quantum mechanics, the sum of energy can fluctuate.
There was a mathematician named Evariste Galois.
He was able to solve many difficult math problems in his teens. Unfortunately, he died at the age of 20.
I can't fall asleep in class. I should try to recite the value of pi...
Not good. I'm falling asleep.
There are 3 laws of motion in mechanics. The law of inertia, the law of motion and the law of cause and effect.
When I fall asleep and hit my head on the desk, my head accelerates and then there is an impact the moment it hits the desk...
Done. I believe I have proved my "falling asleep in class" theory.
Although "perpetual motion" is said to violate thermodynamics laws...
...there are still people who keep looking for the "infinite energy."

Not good. Reading this makes me sleepy...

I got praised for knowing a lot about art history. I'm in perfect form！

People sometimes say, "You did good" when it is supposed to be "You did well."
The traditional Chinese naming system consists of family name, generation name, and given name.
Sometimes there are unusual names like Zhuge Liang - Kong Ming.
A philosopher once said: "What we cannot speak about, we must pass over in silence."
f I can't answer a question, I should try passing it over in silence...

The shogunate system was established under the Kamakura shogunate by Minamoto no Yoritomo.

This is quite interesting, I guess.

I feel terrible today... I'd better fix my art piece.
The teacher praised my drawing. I did really well.
My art piece was praised by the teacher！ I did really well.
High quality paintbrushes are made of sable or badger fur, but mine is just made of synthetic fiber...

I don't think I can make such pieces in class, though.
We have different categories of art such as fine arts, pure arts, etc.
I wonder what kind of art it is we are learning at school...

Arts and sciences are sometimes inseparable, huh？

I'm in bad shape. I can't remember the notes at all.

The teacher praised my music performance. I did great！

I know the theory but it is still very difficult for me.

Most instruments in modern Western music are tuned in the equal temperament system.
A body of singers who perform together as a group is called a choir or chorus.
It's not easy and requires a lot of practice.
Any string instrument that is bowed may informally be called a fiddle, including violins. Sometimes I get confused.
Classical music sounds boring to some people, whereas modern music sounds exciting to them. It depends on preferences.
I'm in great form. Somehow, I feel extremely energetic.
I feel awful today. I can hardly move my body...
Yes！ I set the record in our class's race. I did very well.
Yeah！ I did amazingly well this time！

When we say football, it can mean soccer, rugby, or American football...
They are all different. I only play soccer at school though.
It's very important to properly stretch before exercising.
Sometimes we refer to physical education as gym class, P.E., or Phys. Ed.
Rather than the decathlon, the more common event that high school students participate in is the octathlon.
I'm in a good mood today. I'll be doing my best！
I'm in a crummy mood. I don't feel like doing anything.
All right, I'm in awesome form！ I'll try not to forget this feeling.
I won against our senior！ I was in great form！
I hear the tennis score-keeping word "love" comes from a French word meaning egg.
I know that 0 looks like an egg, but then why don't they just say zero？
In tennis, whenever the score is tied, it is called "deuce."
In Japanese, sometimes we pronounce "deuce" as "juice"...
Many French words are used in tennis terms. I guess the word "tennis" itself is French, too.
The French word "tenir," means "to take heed." It is a warning from the server to the receiver.
The history of tennis goes way back to many centuries ago.
There was a game called "Jeu de paume" during the 16th century and it is believed to be the precursor of tennis.
Traditionally, a tennis racket's strings are made of animal intestines known as catgut.
Nowadays, catgut has been replaced by synthetic materials such as nylon and other polymers.

There are laws specific for libraries although I don't know much about them.
And even school libraries have their own laws.
Usually, the school librarian is just a regular teacher who takes charge, and not the real librarian.
Libraries do not only store books and reading materials.
There are map collections in the libraries as well.
Things went smoothly today. I'll keep doing my best！
Things didn't go so well today. I'm exhausted...
Things went well today. I feel good！
I could deal with problems nicely. I'm feeling good.

Dixie's is a franchise, so it has its own brand awareness. Anyway, seems like the manager has to work really hard.
Dixie's is in the food service industry, but we are different from pizza delivery places or lunch vendors.

Not good. I'm sleepy. I can't concentrate on studying like this at all.

I solved a very difficult problem. It felt great！
I think I can draw a regular heptadecagon with just a compass and a ruler. Let's try it！
What a pain... But somehow I have a feeling of achievement...
I think I might be able to get help with my homework on the net...
No, no. I had better try to do it by myself.
I just have to keep studying and practicing.
That's how I can be a good student.
Homework is supposed to be done at home. What we do in class is called classwork.

Now I can write them correctly without even thinking. This must be the result from all that work back then, huh？

I don't feel well. I can hardly move my body....

I can move my body easily today. Somehow, I'm in great form！

If I keep it up, maybe I will be a muscular man some day.

Yoga has been quite popular lately, but it actually started back in ancient India.
Yoga doesn't just train your body, but your mind and soul as well.
